Title: Build Run -
WorkoutDescription: Run as warm up 10mins E1 10mins E2A Build 50mins with 1 min walk between sections 1.10mins @ E2A 2.10mins @ E2B low 3.10mins @E2B high 4.10mins @E3 5.10mins @AT Warmdown 10mins E1
CoachComments: We are starting at aerobic threshold here and working our way down broken by 1min walk so there should be a distinct change of pace through each section. Don't cook it, I'd prefer you were more conservative over the first 3 sections and bring it home.

Title: Open Water 70.3 Count/Rating Fartlek Focus
WorkoutDescription: Warm up- 10mins easy 5mins @ E2B low . Set 4x 5mins or 400meters on 90seconds stop recovery as - 30 strokes easy / 50 strokes 70.3 rating and pace. . Warmdown Easy 10-15mins.
CoachComments: The focus during the set is to count, Rate and Pace. When you are on the easy 30 strokes just go very easy and relaxed. Once you hit the 70.3 sections of 50-focus on rating up and swimming with focus and pace. There is a 90 seconds stop recovery, that is there to allow you to refocus and let the lactate come off. If you can't organise open water for this it will apply in the pool as the equiv of 400 meter reps

Title: Open Water @ SE wetsuit and paddles
WorkoutDescription: Warm up 10mins E1 SE Set- 4x 600 wetsuit and paddles on 90seconds recovery on beach @ E2B range. Warm down 10mins E1
CoachComments: This is an SE sessions so you want the range of intensity at around the E2B level. (Aerobic Threshold) It is An upper aerobic effort (ie) you are still at aerobic rates but as fast as you go within that range. Breathing becomes deeper but is still controlled and free of oxygen debt. The faster and more efficient you get in this range the more all the ranges will shift.

Title: Program Notes
WorkoutDescription: Hi Aaron, A power SE focus for 2 sessions this week on the bike. Also a mix of some tempo endurance on the run and some speed Wed. Whenever there is key SE, speed or longer sessions I think it's important to focus on recovery through your eating and recovery practises post training especially with regard to protein / Carb intake within the first 35mins post training, if you dont you will put your recovery in the box but more importantly you will stress your immune system because its always the first thing to go when the energy in / energy out ratio gets out of whack. I would supplement protein post sessions and eat to recover. Really important to keep in mind that in the first 35mins the uptake into the muscle beds is much faster and I know it's easy to get busy doing other things but a little routine around this will really help your consistency with training. This is a demanding week, try not to make story of the fatigue, play the cards like you chose them but be discerning enough to the know the difference between being tired and being ruined. My job is to push for adaption, but I am not in your body, sometimes pulling back is what takes us forward, preserving the consistency is important. If you are lacking sleep, have stressful days then dial out intensity and/or volume. Have a ripper week, Cheers, Gilesy.

Title: Descending RPM 75-55 / 1min power - Builder
WorkoutDescription: warm up o 5mins @ E1 85rpm, o 5mins @ E2a 90rpm, o 3mins @ E2b 95rpm o 1mins @ E3 100rpm o 3mins @ RC- E1 70- 80rpm easy rolling . Main Set 5x 7mins E2B Turbo o 2mins @ 75rpm o 2mins @ 65rpm o 2mins @ 55rpm o 1min hard from the 55rpm gear smoothly 4mins ezy between each rep . Warm down- Ezy 10mins small gears low load.
CoachComments: This 7min effort is a progressively lower cadence but we are looking for nothing over E2B for the first 6mins -as that cadence lowers it gets more difficult to get a heart rate response so keep it as prescribed. In the last minute you are going from the gear you in at 55rpm for 60 seconds hard, then it's 4mins in light gears just spinning. Maintain you focus over that first 6 mins to make sure you are as smooth as you can be-think/feel perfect circles.

Title: Track 200's
WorkoutDescription: Warmup as- 1600 Meters E1 1600 Meters E2A-E2B low . Main Set- 12x 200 @ threshold on 200 walk back recovery. . Warm down- 1200 E2A 1000 easy float.
CoachComments: TRACK VERSION: This session overspeed. But focus on turnover here. Start the effort building leg speed. Start the rep with feet shoulder width apart and lean from the ankles until you feel your toes claw the ground, this is correct lean angle, fall forward from that stance and let the leg speed come. Flow, relax and let it happen, by the end of the rep you want to be fast. The recovery is walk/jog, as slowly as you need to refract to the next rep. You can also do these as jog/walk back to start. NON TRACK VERSION: If you can't get to track all you need a 200 meter stretch of road or field. Walk/jog back to start. If that is the case the warm up becomes 8mins E1, 8mins E2A. Warm down 8mins E2A, 5mins E1.

Title: AT/FTP Peppering -E2B recovery
WorkoutDescription: warm up o 5mins @ E1 85rpm, o 5mins @ E2a 90rpm, o 3mins @ E2b 95rpm o 1mins @ E3 100rpm o 1mint VO2 Trans 95-110rpm o 5mins @ RC- E1 70- 80rpm easy rolling . Set 1 4x 5mins on 2mins rec at 90-102% of AT plus or minus 5bpm on 75-85rpm . Recovery -10mins easy rolling @ E1 . Repeat first set  Set 2 4x 5mins on 2mins rec at 90-102% of AT plus or minus 5bpm on 85-90rpm Finish the ride very aerobic to round out volume
CoachComments: Session is about really peppering your IAT workload for short periods of time on low rest periods, so we are working close to FTP on the button with little rest. It looks straight forward, it's a lot of work, you'll need good fuel post session. Also have a second look at cadence, there's an SE component hidden here, the best strength builder of all, SE, power and AT. Potent mix, needs fuel.

Title: Psych Tip for sessions today - Reactivity #1
WorkoutDescription: Before the start of the sessions today take 5 mins to center yourself. Take the time to sit and contemplate the following four statements, align yourself with them and focus on them completely brining yourself into presence with the sessions and allowing the events of the day to dissolve.
CoachComments: o Its all about how you react, the session has no power over you other than the power you give it. o Victimhood is a thought, that has a reaction in the body, don't fuel it, suffocate it. o Resistance is futility in action.

Title: Endurance low aerobic
WorkoutDescription: Low aerobic 60mins @ sub E1. Pedaling at all times but at light intensity to preserve power and keep legs supple.

Title: Track 200's #2
WorkoutDescription: Warmup as- 1600 Meters E1 1600 Meters E2A-E2B low . Main Set- 12x 200 @ threshold on 200 walk back recovery. . Warm down- 1200 E2A 1000 easy float.
CoachComments: TRACK VERSION: This session overspeed. But focus on turnover here. Start the effort building leg speed. Start the rep with feet shoulder width apart and lean from the ankles until you feel your toes claw the ground, this is correct lean angle, fall forward from that stance and let the leg speed come. Flow, relax and let it happen, by the end of the rep you want to be fast. The recovery is walk/jog, as slowly as you need to refract to the next rep. You can also do these as jog/walk back to start. NON TRACK VERSION: If you can't get to track all you need a 200 meter stretch of road or field. Walk/jog back to start. If that is the case the warm up becomes 8mins E1, 8mins E2A. Warm down 8mins E2A, 5mins E1.

Title: Low hrate run - Strides
WorkoutDescription: A 70min dead flat run. Run at the lowest possible oxygen cost for the best form. Incorporate 5x 60seconds building to high turnover on the 3min cycle.
CoachComments: This run is about fat burning low aerobic run form. Don't run so slow that the form is hampered but run where you are most comfortable on a cross benefit of form and function

Title: Open Water Beach start 200s
WorkoutDescription: Beach start warm up 15 mins set 10x 200 with a flying 100 from the beach to turn then a cruise 100 back to shore. Partice high speed through start warm down 15mins easy lope
CoachComments: The focus here is start. Try to start and have less breaths at the start (ie) stroking 4-5 times without breath, remember though not to hold breath - breathe it out over the entire time your head is in the water.

Title: Short Speed Reps
WorkoutDescription: Warm up- 400 free every 4th 50 bk 8x 50 first drill on 50 building . Set- speed 1800 16x 25 @ high speed leave on 45 seconds 200 float easy 8x 50 @ speed leave on 2mins 200 float easy 4x 100 @ speed leave on 2:30 200 float easy . 8x 50 pull sub E1 on 15 rest.
CoachComments: The focus here for main set is speed. We are looking for high rating through the 25/50 sets but relax at the same time. Focus on pulling your body across your arms and apply the force through your lats not your shoulders.

Title: Notes-Race Week Phuket
WorkoutDescription: Hi Aaron, Lets not reinvent the wheel here, so keep everything as close to normal this week as possible including this taper. Set it and forget it... Now is the time to empty your head and make this approach as simple as you possibly can. We want you on the line fresh and healthy. So its the same taper to eliminate any doubts. Keep it simple, do your grounding, stay with yourself. Breathe, relax the tension in the front of your body constantly and consistently. Keep this super simple and enough here to keep you moving. Keep yourself calm, breathe often this week and prepare to go deep. Don't change anything. Don't go looking for more. Let the racing do the work. Avoid touching it up in training. Don't test, trust! Cheers, Gilesy.

Take the time to sit and contemplate the following four statements, align yourself with them and focus on them completely brining yourself into presence with the sessions and allowing the events of the day to dissolve.
CoachComments: o False Evidence Appearing Real. o Fear lives in only two places=Past and future, it cannot live in the present. o Life provides the necessary responses for survival; the multiplication of mind is not needed. o Dont let the emotion rise into the mind and become a fear story. Break the fear circuit by feeling it.

Title: Aerobic Threshold Bike
WorkoutDescription: Run as warm up 20mins E1 20mins E2A Build 40mins with 4 min recco between sections 4x 10mins @ aerobic threshold =E2B mid. Warmdown 40mins E1
CoachComments: (Aerobic Threshold) It is An upper aerobic effort (ie) you are still at aerobic rates but as fast as you go within that range. Breathing becomes deeper but is still controlled and free of oxygen debt. The faster and more efficient you get in this range the more all the ranges will shift.

Title: Program Notes - Power
WorkoutDescription: Hi Aaron, This week is as specific. Its targeted on developing threshold. A week like this is not made of pushing and forcing, its made of relaxing and accepting. So as each set starts, guide yourself to as much ease as you can rather than tension. Forget trying to known this thing with your brain and try to understand it with your body, be the tuning fork to it, not the assessment officer. Its a pretty tough week made of tough sessions, great opportunity to bring yourself to it fully attentive. If you have any problems with the structure here please let me know. Have a great week, Cheers, Gilesy.

Title: Psych Tip for sessions today - Non Resistance #1
WorkoutDescription: Pre session prep 5 mins contemplate and relaxed breathing. o Don't go into resistance with what you are about to do. Where focus goes, the energy flows. o The body will follow the thought patterns, any form of resistance is quickly followed by contraction. o Take the "re" out of reaction and you get action. o What you resist persists.

Title: Speed Endurance
WorkoutDescription: Warm up- 8x 50 first drill on 50 building Set 1- speed 3000 10x 100 fast but soft leaving on 30 rest 800 pull sub E1 5x 100 fast but soft leave 30 rest 300 pull sub E1 8x 50 fast on 60seconds rest . set 2 5x 100 30 rest very easy pull paddles . Warmdown Easy 200 mix.
CoachComments: These speed sets are set to fast, but relax as much as you can. Sounds like a paradox but it isn't, focus on your relaxation at speed.

Title: Speedplay 50s
WorkoutDescription: Warm Up- 400 free every 4th 50 bk 8x 50 first drill on 50 building . Set-1 Aerobic rhythm set / Paddles/Pull set as- 2x 1000 on 60secs break on E2B low even pace . Main set 40x 50 / broken as follows 1) 16x 50 / every 4th hard on 45 2) 12x 50 / every 3rd hard on 50 3) 8x 50 / every 2nd hard on 55 4) 4x 50 / every one hard on 60 . Warm Down- 300 pull sub E1 800 pull very easy, every 4th b/k

Title: Track 1000's
WorkoutDescription: Warmup as- 1600 Meters E1 1600 Meters E2A-E2B low . Main Set- 5x 1000 AT+ on 400 walk/float recovery. ave 2:55-3km pace. . Warm down- 1000 easy float.
CoachComments: If this session cannot be done as track then do it as fartlek as- Warm up- 7mins E1 7mins E2A-E2B low . Main Set- 5x 3:30mins mid AT on 2:30 walk/float recovery. . Warm down - 7mins easy float. ...................... Run the 1000 or 3:30mins on the low to mid threshold range. Don't blow your candles out by going overspeed. This is about the function of the whole session so we are looking for flow and function. Float the recovery by walking 200, then jog the next 200 keeping the heart rate at about 75-80% so its not totally off on the 200 float. We want your heart rate to come off but not totally off. Be careful not to overdo the first 500, let it build.

Title: AT Endurance Control Focus (Builder)
WorkoutDescription: Warmup pyramid as- o 5mins @ E1 85rpm, o 5mins @ E2a 90rpm, o 3mins @ E2b 95rpm o 1mins @ E3 100rpm o 3mins @ RC- E1 70- 80rpm easy rolling . AT Endurance Control Focus o 3x 4mins / AT low / rec 2min ezy 5mins ezy spin o 3x 3mins / AT sustained / rec 1 min 5mins ezy spin o 3x 2mins / Sprint =AT + 5 / 30secs rec . Warm down Easy gears to finish out ride volume.
CoachComments: This is an intense set. You'll need good control at the start. I want the cadence range at 80rpm please so yes it will be a big gear. Don't change the cadence at all, just use the gears to raise your intensity level. Feel into this one and have a look at the whole set before you start so you have a good sense of what is in front of you and that control will be key. Make your intensity change smooth, don't panic work on the feel and the form even in the AT+ range and work hard on not judging in your mind what is happening -let pain be there and accept everything you feel. Practice now so it comes out in races.

WorkoutDescription: Pre session prep 5 mins contemplate and relaxed breathing. o Don't go into resistance with what you are about to do. Where focus goes, the energy flows. o The body will follow the thought patterns, any form of resistance is quickly followed by contraction. o Take the "re" out of reaction and you get action. o Don't go after mental pictures and measure how it looks in your head against what is happening, stay where you are, and work with that, not matter how much discomfort emerges, you will learn more from than in 30mins than you will from 4 hours of feeling good.

Title: Open Water
WorkoutDescription: 15mins warm up main set 5x 400 as fartlek 2x{ 100 out surge +race pace 100 back in E2B Beach recovery 2mins 15mins warm down
CoachComments: This session is about start practise. So from the beach try to chase a pace off the beach that is realistic to race start, really go for it then change the pace back to E2B and try to recovery while still at a decent clip. This is very trainable and a skill worth having in your back pocket.
